<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="80" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,822,847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Tergite 7 triangular, bearing a pair of short posterolateral projections; sternite 7 broad, extended laterally, bearing a pair of posterolateral, pointed projections; parameres elongate, with spatulate subapical expansion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,930,955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Body length approximately 2.0 mm (
<figureCitation box="[843,907,930,955]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[166,1371,529,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus, lateral view, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262475/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A). Brownish species in general colour. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1365,1436,930,955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Head.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,227,966,991]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,214,1192]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1202]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., male: A. lateral view, B. frontal view. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) Shining black, longer than wide; eyes large, holoptic, with short hairs between facets; ommatidia equal in size, in lateral view at level of base of scape, a row of 7 ommatidia disposed from outer to inner ocular margin; three ocelli, equal in size; antennae (
<figureCitation box="[563,632,1038,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,214,1192]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1202]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., male: A. lateral view, B. frontal view. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[645,658,1039,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1968,1990]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,926,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,918,1946]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Flagellum, lateral view, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.04 mm. Flag = flagellum (Flagellomeres I – VIII); Ped = pedicel, Sc = scape.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262477/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">3</figureCitation>
A) uniformly brown, longer than head-height; scape square, a row of setae disposed along to distal margin; pedicel subcylindrical, 8 flagellomeres covered with microtrichia and sensilla; flagellomeres I–VII twice as wide as long, each bearing a whorl of setae, last flagellomere rounded, as long as 2 preceding ones, bearing 3 whorls of setae; flagellum length, 
<quantity box="[980,1087,1146,1171]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
; frontoclypeus setose; occiput pilose, with a pair of lateral sensilla; small internal sclerotized sclerite at base of labella, as long as palpus; palpi (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1218,1243]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,214,1192]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1202]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Head. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., male: A. lateral view, B. frontal view. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[243,257,1219,1243]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1966,1988]" captionTargetBox="[277,1299,211,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[259,1315,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Palpus, lateral view, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.04 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">4</figureCitation>
A) brown, setose, subcylindrical, apically rounded, with at least 3–4 subapical sensory pits, length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
; labella shorter than palpi; cardo-stipes setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1290,1315]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Thorax.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[314,381,1290,1315]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1916,1938]" captionTargetBox="[166,1371,529,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus, lateral view, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262475/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A, 5) Dark brown; mesonotum narrow, much longer than wide, covered with dense short pilosity, a well-marked row of 10–12 supraalar setae, scutellum with a row of 12–14 elongate marginal setae; anterior spiracular sclerite setose (9–12 setae), with a well-marked antero-dorsal pointed projection, spiracle large, not longer than high (
<figureCitation box="[424,499,1398,1423]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[155,1433,199,1128]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1134]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Thorax, anterior spiracular sclerite, frontal view, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.05 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262480/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A); pleural setae: 9–13 anepisternal, in upper anterior corner of sclerite, 5–8 anepimeral, 6–9 subalar, 3–4 katepisternal, 4–5 posterior spiracular, no meral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1470,1495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Wing.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[293,368,1470,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1905,1927]" captionTargetBox="[157,1409,1268,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,1258,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Wings, male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. Aztecatopse neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A) length, 
<quantity box="[503,676,1471,1495]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.295" metricValueMax="1.32" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="1.295" valueMax="1.32" valueMin="1.27">1.27–1.32 mm</quantity>
, width, 
<quantity box="[781,954,1470,1495]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.949999999999999" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.699999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="0.595" valueMax="0.62" valueMin="0.57">0.57–0.62 mm</quantity>
; membrane with dense microtrichia; no macrotrichia on membrane except the usual row along the posterior margin; R1 and R4+5 with an irregularly arranged row of short setae dorsally; R4+5 reaching costa beyond middle of wing, and slightly beyond level of fork of M; M fork nearly twice as long as stem, gradually widening towards wing margin; second costal section shorter than first; a false vein present between M2 and CuA1; CuA2 smoothly angled near middle, reaching wing margin obliquely. Wing length/section costal 1: 2.8; WL/C2: 7.2; WL/C3: 1.9; WL/C1+C2: 2.04; C extending 0.51 of wing length. Halters brown, bearing a row of 3–4 setae on stem.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1731,1756]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Legs.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[277,344,1731,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,838,860]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,200,802]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,817]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Legs, lateral view, male: Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov. A. fore, B. mid, C. hind. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262482/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) Concolourous with body, tarsi somewhat lighter, especially the posterior ones; comb of setae on posteroapical part of hind tibia well developed; first tarsomere of posterior leg longer than second.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,570,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1803,1828]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites and sternites shining. Tergites with pilosity much reduced on anterior segments, becoming denser on posterior segments. Tergite 2 with well defined sublateral lunula-like pretergites. Sternite 1 unsclerotized, 2 to seven normally sclerotized, regularly beset with pilosity and micropilosity; segment 7 with a narrow anterior ring of sclerotization joining tergite and sternite; tergite 7 triangular, short, pilose, bearing a pair of posterolateral, short projections (
<figureCitation box="[542,620,1947,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,210,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1903]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Seventh abdominal segment (tergite (Tg), dorsal view, sternite (St), ventral view), male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262483/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Figs 9</figureCitation>
A, 10A), heavier sclerotized than rest of segment; posterior margin rounded; length, 
<quantity box="[346,451,1983,2008]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
, width, 
<quantity box="[544,650,1983,2007]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" unit="mm" value="0.32">0.32 mm</quantity>
. Sternite 7 wider than long, slightly emarginate anteriorly, expanded laterally, bearing a pair of posterolateral, pointed projections; posterior emargination of the sternite complex, deeply V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[352,423,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,210,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1903]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 9. Seventh abdominal segment (tergite (Tg), dorsal view, sternite (St), ventral view), male: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm.)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262483/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Figs 9</figureCitation>
A, 10A); median zone of sternite 7 close to posterior margin ornamented, bearing a cluster of small rounded granulations; length, 
<quantity box="[616,724,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
, width, 
<quantity box="[826,935,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" unit="mm" value="0.37">0.37 mm</quantity>
. Genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1242,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1968,1990]" captionTargetBox="[404,1176,212,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[394,1191,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male genital capsule: A. Aztecatopse amorimi sp. nov., B. A. foliosa sp. nov., C. A. neotropica sp. nov., D. A. spinosa sp. nov. (Scale bar = 0.1 mm). Left side, ventral view; right side, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262485/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Figs 11</figureCitation>
A, 12) elongate, epandrium triangular, posterior margin prolonged into a sclerotized plough-like process; gonocoxites joined to epandrium, medial lobe setose, a pair of straight, flattened processes; aedeagus long and thick, pilose apically; parameres elongate, bearing a ventromedian, short spine, with a spatulate subapical expansion; sperm-duct elongate, enlarged, with comparatively small vesica.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,464]" box="[199,417,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
