<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1356,1381]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after our friend and colleague Dr. Dalton de Souza Amorim, for his outstanding contribution to the systematics and phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1017,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scatopsidae</taxonomicName>
of the world.
</paragraph>
